  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer for the People"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer for the People"
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of Nehemiah son of Hacaliah. It happened in the month of
        Kislev, in the twentieth year, that I myself was in the citadel in Susa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and one of my brothers, Hanani, came with some men from Judah. I
        asked them about the Jews who had escaped the captivity and about Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They replied to me, \u201CThe survivors in the province who have
        survived the captivity are in great trouble and disgrace. The wall of Jerusalem
        is broken down, and its gates have been burned in the fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When I heard these words, I sat and wept and mourned for days, and
        I was fasting and praying before the God of the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I said, \u201CO Yahweh God of the heavens, the great and awesome
        one who keeps the covenant and loyal love for the ones who love him and for
        those who keep his commands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Please, let your ear be attentive and your eyes open to hear the
        prayer of your servant that I am praying before you by day and by night for
        your servants, the Israelites, and confessing the sins of the Israelites
        that we have sinned against you. I and my father\u2019s house have sinned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We have certainly offended you and have not kept the commands, regulations,
        and judgments that you have commanded your servant Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Please, remember the word that you have commanded to your servant
        Moses, saying, \u2018If you act unfaithfully I will scatter you all among
        the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But if you return to me and keep my commandments and do them, even
        though all of your outcasts are at the furthest parts of heaven, I will gather
        them and bring them to the place which I have chosen to make my name dwell.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They are your servants and your people whom you have redeemed by
        your great power and by your strong hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "O Lord, please let your ear be attentive to the prayer of your servant
        and to the prayer of your servants who delight to revere in your name. Please,
        let your servant be successful this day and give him compassion before this
        man.\u201D I was cupbearer for the king. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Sent'
      title: Nehemiah Sent
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened in the month of Nisan, in the twentieth year of King
        Artaxerxes, when wine was before him, I carried the wine and gave it to the
        king. And I had never been sad before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the king said to me, \u201CWhy is your face sad since you are
        not sick? This is nothing but sadness of the heart.\u201D And I was very
        much afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I said to the king, \u201CMay the king live forever! Why should my
        face not be sad when the city of my ancestors\u2019 burial site is ruined
        and her gates are consumed by fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to me, \u201CWhat is your request?\u201D So I
        prayed to the God of the heavens. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, and if your
        servant has found favor in your presence, I ask that you send me to Judah,
        to the city of my ancestors\u2019 burial sites, so that I may rebuild it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "With the queen sitting beside him, the king said to me, \u201CHow
        long will your journey be and when will you return?\u201D So it pleased the
        king and he sent me, and I set for him an appointed time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said to the king, \u201CIf it is good for the king, let letters
        be given to me for the governors in the province Beyond the River, that they
        may let me pass until I come to Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also, a letter to Asaph, keeper of the king\u2019s land reserve,
        that he should give me timber for laying the beams for the gates of the citadel
        of the house and for the walls of the city, and for the house which I will
        enter.\u201D And the king gave permission to me, according to the good hand
        of God on me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I came to the governors of the province Beyond the River, and I gave
        them the letters of the king. Then the king sent troop commanders and horses
        with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Nehemiah Inspects the Walls and Decides to Restore Them'
      title: Nehemiah Inspects the Walls and Decides to Restore Them
      number: 10
      content: 'But when Sanballat the Horonite and the Ammonite servant Tobiah heard
        this, they were greatly displeased that a person had come to seek the welfare
        of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I came to Jerusalem and was there for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I got up during the night, I and a few men with me. I did not tell
        anybody what my God put in my heart to do for Jerusalem. No animal was with
        me except the animal that I was riding on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I went out during the night at the gate of the valley by the Dragon
        spring and to the Dung Gate. And I examined the walls in Jerusalem and its
        gates that had been destroyed by the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I crossed over to the Fountain Gate and to the King\u2019s Pool,
        but there was no place for my mount to cross over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I went up by the valley during the night and was examining the
        wall. Then I returned and came to the Valley Gate and returned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The prefects did not know where I had gone and what I was doing.
        I had not yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the prefects, and the
        rest of the workers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I said to them, \u201CYou see the misery that we are in, that
        Jerusalem is ruined and its gates burned by the fire. Come, build the walls
        of Jerusalem and we shall no longer be a disgrace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I told them of the good hand of my God that was upon me and surely
        the words of the king that were spoken to me. And they said, \u201CLet us
        arise and build!\u201D And they strengthened their hands for this good work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Sanballat the Horonite, the Ammonite servant Tobiah, and Geshem
        the Arab heard it, and they mocked and despised us, saying, \u201CWhat is
        this thing that you are doing? Are you rebelling against the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then I answered and said to them, \u201CThe God of the heavens himself
        will let us succeed, and we his servants shall arise and build. But for you
        there is no share, right, or memorial in Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Organization of the Work'
      title: Organization of the Work
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliashib the high priest and his brothers the priests arose
        and rebuilt the Sheep Gate. They consecrated it and erected its doors. They
        consecrated it up to the Tower of the Hundred and up to the Tower of Hananel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And next to him the men of Jericho built, and next to him Zaccur
        son of Imri built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Hassenaah built the Fish Gate. They laid its beams and
        erected its doors, its bolts, and its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Next to them Meremoth son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz, repaired. Next
        to them Meshullam son of Berekiah, son of Meshezabel, repaired. Next to them
        Zadok son of Baana repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Next to them the Tekoites repaired, but their nobles did not put
        their neck to the work of their lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Jehoiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam repaired the old Yeshanah
        Gate. They laid its beams and erected its doors, its bolts, and its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Next to them Melatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite, the
        men of Gibeon and Mizpah who were under the rule of the governor of the province
        Beyond the River, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Next to him Uzziel son of Harhaiah (goldsmiths) repaired. Next to
        him Hananiah son of the perfume-makers repaired. They restored Jerusalem
        up to the Broad Wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Next to them Rephaiah son of Hur, commander of half the district
        of Jerusalem, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Next to them Jedaiah son of Harumaph repaired opposite his house.
        Next to him Hattush son of Hashabneiah repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Malkijah son of Harim and Hasshub son of Pahath-Moab repaired another
        section and the Tower of the Ovens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next to him Shallum son of Hallohesh, commander of half of the district
        of Jerusalem, repaired with his daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired the Valley Gate. They
        rebuilt it and erected its doors, its bolts, and its bars, and a thousand
        cubits of the wall up to the Dung Gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Malkijah son of Recab, commander of the district of Beth-haccherem,
        repaired the Dung Gate. He rebuilt it and erected its doors, its bolts, and
        its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Shallun son of Col-Hozeh, the commander of the district of Mizpah,
        repaired the Fountain Gate. He rebuilt it and covered it and erected its
        doors, its bolts, its bars, and he built the wall of the Pool of Shelah of
        the king\u2019s garden, right up to the steps going down from the city of
        David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After him Nehemiah son of Azbuk, commander of half of the district
        of Beth Zur, repaired up to a point opposite the burial sites of David, and
        up to the artificial pool and to the house of the mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After him the Levites repaired; Rehum son of Bani, and next to him
        Hashabiah, commander of half of the district of Keilah, repaired his district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After him their brothers repaired: Bavvai son of Henadad, commander
        of half of the district of Keilah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'next to him Ezer son of Jeshua, commander of Mizpah, repaired a second
        section of a wall opposite of the ascent of the armory at the angle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After him Baruch son of Zabbai zealously repaired a second section
        of a wall from the angle up to the doorway of the house of Eliashib the high
        priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'After him Meremoth son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz, repaired a second
        section of a wall from the doorway of the house of Eliashib up to the end
        of the house of Eliashib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After him the priests, men from the vicinity, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After them Benjamin and Hasshub repaired opposite their house. After
        them Azariah son of Maaseiah, son of Ananiah, repaired beside his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After him Binnui son of Henadad repaired a second section of a wall
        from the house of Azariah up to the angle up to the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Palal son of Uzai repaired opposite the Angle at the tower that juts
        out from the upper house of the king, at the courtyard of the guard. After
        him Pedaiah son of Parosh '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and the temple servants who were living on Ophel repaired up to opposite
        the Water Gate on the east and the projecting tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'After him the Tekoites repaired a second section of a wall opposite
        the projecting tower that goes out as far as the wall of Ophel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Above the Horse Gate the priests repaired, each one opposite his
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'After them Zadok son of Immer repaired opposite his house. After
        him Shemaiah son of Shecaniah, keeper of the East Gate, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After him Hananiah son of Shelemiah and Hanun the sixth son of Zalaph
        repaired another section. After him Meshullam son of Berekiah repaired the
        wall opposite his room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'After him Malkijah, one of the goldsmiths, repaired up to the house
        of the temple servants and the merchants, opposite the Enrollment Gate and
        up to the upper room of the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Between the upper room of the corner to the Sheep Gate the goldsmiths
        and merchants repaired. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Opposition Begins'
      title: Opposition Begins
      number: 1
      content: ' Now it happened when Sanballat heard that we were building the wall,
        he became angry and greatly provoked, and he mocked the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he said before his brothers and the army of Samaria, \u201CWhat
        are the feeble Jews doing? Will they restore these things for themselves?
        Will they sacrifice? Will they finish it in a day? Will they revive the stones
        from the piles of rubble\u2014even those burned up?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him and said, \u201CTheir wall of
        stone that they are building would break down if a fox went on it!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear, our God, for we are despised. Turn their scorn on their head
        and give them over to plunder in the land of captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not cover their guilt, and do not let their sin be blotted out
        from before you. They have provoked the builders to anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Opposition Stopped'
      title: Opposition Stopped
      number: 6
      content: 'So we rebuilt the wall, and all of the wall was joined up to half
        its height. For the people had a heart to do it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when Sanballat, Tobiah, the Arabs, the Ammonites, and the Ashdodites
        heard that the restoration of the walls of Jerusalem were going forward and
        the gaps were being closed, they were very angry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So all of them plotted together to come fight against Jerusalem and
        to make trouble for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So we prayed to our God and set up a guard against them day and night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Judah said, \u201CThe strength of the carriers is failing, and
        there is too much dirt, and we are not able to build at the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then our enemies said, \u201CThey will not know nor see until we
        come upon them and will kill them and stop the work.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the Jews who lived beside them came, they said to us ten times,
        \u201CFrom all of the places where they live, they will come up against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I stationed the people behind the deepest part of the wall in the
        open places according to their families, with their swords, spears, and bows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I looked, got up, and said to the nobles, prefects, and the rest
        of the people, \u201CDo not be afraid of them. Remember the Lord, who is
        great and awesome, and fight for your brothers, your sons, your daughters,
        your wives, and your houses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "It happened when our enemies heard that their plan was known to us,
        that God had frustrated it, and we all returned to the wall\u2014each to
        his work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'From that day, half of my servants were working on craftsmanship,
        half were holding spears, small shields, bows, and breastplates. The commanders
        were behind the whole house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The ones who were building the wall and the ones who carried the
        materials were carrying in one hand while doing the task, and with the other
        hand were grasping a weapon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Each of the builders had his sword tied to his side while building.
        And the man who sounded the trumpet was beside me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I said to the nobles, to the prefects, and to the rest of the people,
        \u201CThe work is great and widespread, and we are spread out over the wall
        far from each other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Wherever you hear the sound of the trumpet, come together to us there.
        Our God will fight for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So we labored at the work, and half of them were holding the spears
        from dawn until the stars came out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "At the time I also said to the people, \u201CLet each man and his
        servant spend the night inside Jerusalem, so that they will be a guard for
        us in the night and work in the day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So neither I nor my brothers nor my young men nor the men of the
        guard who were behind me took off our clothes. Each one kept his weapon even
        in the water. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Deals with Strife'
      title: Nehemiah Deals with Strife
      number: 1
      content: 'Now there was a great cry of distress of the people and of their
        wives against their Jewish brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "There were those who were saying, \u201COur sons and daughters, we
        are many. We must get grain so that we may eat and live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There were also those saying, \u201CWe have pledged our fields and
        our vineyards and our houses so that we can get grain in the famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And there were those who were saying, \u201CWe have borrowed money
        on our fields and our vineyards for the tax of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now our flesh is like the flesh of our brothers, our sons are like
        their sons. Look, we are subduing our sons and our daughters to be slaves,
        and there are some from our daughters being molested. We are powerless, and
        our fields and vineyards belong to others.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I was very angry when I heard their shouts and these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought over this in my heart, and then I quarreled with the nobles
        and the prefects. I said to them, \u201CYou yourselves are taking interest
        from your own brother!\u201D So I called the great assembly against them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I said to them: \u201CWe ourselves have bought back our brothers
        the Jews who were sold to the nations as we were able. But now you yourselves
        have sold your brothers so they may be sold to us!\u201D They were silent
        and could not find a word to say. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I said, \u201CThe thing that you are doing is not good. Should
        you not walk in the fear of our God to prevent the disgrace from the nations,
        our enemies? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also, I and my brothers and my servants are lending them money and
        grain. Please stop taking this interest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please restore to them this day their fields, their vineyards, their
        olive groves, their houses, and the interest on the money, the grain, the
        grape juice, and the olive oil that you have been taking from them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So they said, \u201CWe will restore it and will not request anything
        more. So we will do as you say.\u201D Then I called the priests and made
        them take an oath to do this promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Nehemiah Denies His Allotment'
      title: Nehemiah Denies His Allotment
      number: 13
      content: "I also shook out my garment and said, \u201CThis is how God will
        shake out everyone from his house who will not keep this promise. So this
        is how his possessions will be shaken out and emptied.\u201D And all the
        assembly said, \u201CAmen!\u201D And they praised Yahweh, and the people
        kept this promise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Moreover, from the appointed day I was made their governor in the
        land of Judah, from the twentieth year until the thirty-second year of King
        Artaxerxes\u2014twelve years. My brothers and I did not eat the food allowance
        of the governor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The former governors who were before me laid burdens on the people,
        and they took food and wine from them, besides forty shekels. Also, their
        servants controlled the people, but I did not do so because of the fear of
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I also devoted myself to the work of this wall, and we did not buy
        land. All of my servants were gathered for the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'One hundred and fifty men, prefects and Jews, and those who came
        to us from the nations around us, were at my table. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now what was prepared each day for me was one ox, six choice sheep,
        and birds. And every ten days all kinds of wine were made. But for this I
        did not demand the food allowance of the governor because the slavery was
        too heavy on this people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Remember me for good, my God, all that I have done for this people. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Enemies Foiled'
      title: Enemies Foiled
      number: 1
      content: "Now when it was reported to Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and
        to the rest of our enemies that I had built the wall and that no gap was
        left in it\u2014though up to that time I had not erected doors in the gates\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Sanballat and Geshem sent to me, saying, \u201CCome and let us meet
        together in one of the villages in the plain of Ono.\u201D But they planned
        to do evil to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I sent messengers to them, saying, \u201CI am doing a great work
        and I am not able to come down. Why should the work stop while I leave it
        and come down to you all?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they sent a message to me four times like this, and I returned
        an answer like this to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Sanballat sent his servant with an open letter, another word
        like this to me a fifth time, in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In it was written, \u201CIt has been reported among the nations,
        and Gashmu also is saying it, that you and the Jews are considering rebellion.
        Therefore, truly you are building the wall and you are becoming their king,
        according to these words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You have also set up prophets to proclaim in Jerusalem concerning
        you, saying, \u2018There is a king in Judah.\u2019 And now it will be proclaimed
        to the king according to these words. Now, come and we will plan together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So I sent to him saying, \u201CNone of these words you have spoken
        has happened. You are indeed saying things created in your own mind\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "for all of them sought to frighten us, saying, \u201Ctheir hands
        will not do the work.\u201D And now, God, strengthen my hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now I went into the house of Shemaiah son of Delaiah, son of Mehetabel,
        who was confined at home, and he said, \u201CLet us meet in the house of
        God, inside the temple, and let us close the doors of the temple; for they
        are coming to kill you\u2014during the night they are coming to kill you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But I said, \u201CShould a man like me run away? And would a man
        like me go into the temple so that he can save his life? I will not go in!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I look and realized God had not sent him; rather, he had spoken
        the prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For this reason he was hired: to frighten me so that I would act
        and sin, so that they would have a bad report so they could taunt me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Wall is Completed'
      title: The Wall is Completed
      number: 14
      content: 'Remember, O my God, Tobiah and Sanballat according to their works,
        and also Noadiah the prophetess, and the remainder of the prophets who were
        frightening me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth day of Elul, in fifty-two
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When our enemies heard of this, all of the nations surrounding us
        were afraid and lost their confidence. They knew that this work had been
        done with the help of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Also, in those days the nobles of Judah increasingly sent their letters
        to Tobiah, and letters from Tobiah returned to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For many in Judah were bound by oath to him because he was the son-in-law
        of Shecaniah son of Arah. His son Jehohanan took as a wife the daughter of
        Meshullam son of Berekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They also were speaking of his good deeds in my presence, and they
        were sending my words out to him. Tobiah sent letters to intimidate me. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Now when the wall had been built and I had erected the doors and
        appointed the gatekeepers, singers, and the Levites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I gave command over Jerusalem to my brother Hanani and Hananiah the
        commander of the citadel. For he was a faithful man and feared God more than
        many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I said to them, \u201CDo not open the gates of Jerusalem until the
        sun is hot. While they are standing guard let them shut and fasten the doors.
        And appoint guards from the inhabitants of Jerusalem, one at his post and
        another opposite his house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Lists of the Exiles Who Returned'
      title: Lists of the Exiles Who Returned
      number: 4
      content: 'The city was widespread and large, but the people in it were few
        and no houses were rebuilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then my God put into my heart to assemble the nobles, the prefects,
        and the people to be enrolled. I found the book of the genealogy of those
        who first came back, and I found this written upon it: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'These are the people of the province who came up from captivity of
        the exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had carried into exile. They
        returned to Jerusalem and to Judah, each one to his city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These came with Zerubbabel, Joshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani,
        Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah. The number of the men
        of the people of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the descendants of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The descendants of Shephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The descendants of Arah, six hundred and fifty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The descendants of Pahath-Moab, of the descendants of Jeshua and
        Joab, two thousand eight hundred and eighteen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The descendants of Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The descendants of Zattu, eight hundred and forty-five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The descendants of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The descendants of Binnui, six hundred and forty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The descendants of Bebai, six hundred and twenty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The descendants of Azgad, two thousand three hundred and twenty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The descendants of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-seven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The descendants of Bigvai, two thousand and sixty-seven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The descendants of Adin, six hundred and fifty-five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The descendants of Ater, namely of Hezekiah, ninety-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The descendants of Hashum, three hundred and twenty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The descendants of Bezai, three hundred and twenty-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The descendants of Hariph, one hundred and twelve. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The descendants of Gibeon, ninety-five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The men of Bethlehem and Netophah, one hundred and eighty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The men of Beth-azmaveth, forty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The men of Kiriath-Jearim, Kephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and
        forty-three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The men of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The men of Micmash, one hundred and twenty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The men of Bethel and Ai, one hundred and twenty-three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The men of the other Nebo, fifty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The people of the other Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The people of Harim, three hundred and twenty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The people of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The people of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, seven hundred and twenty-one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The people of Senaah, three thousand nine hundred and thirty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The priests: The descendants of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua,
        nine hundred and seventy-three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The descendants of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The descendants of Pashhur, one thousand two hundred and forty-seven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The descendants of Harim, one thousand and seventeen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The Levites: the descendants of Jeshua, namely of Kadmiel of the
        descendants of Hodaviah, seventy-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The singers: the descendants of Asaph, one hundred and forty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The gatekeepers: the descendants of Shallum, the descendants of Ater,
        the descendants of Talmon, the descendants of Akkub, the descendants of Hatita,
        the descendants of Shobai, one hundred and thirty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The temple servants: the descendants of Ziha, the descendants of
        Hasupha, the descendants of Tabbaoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'the descendants of Keros, the descendants of Siaha, the descendants
        of Padon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'the descendants of Lebanah, the descendants of Hagaba, the descendants
        of Shalmai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'the descendants of Hanan, the descendants of Giddel, the descendants
        of Gahar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'the descendants of Reaiah, the descendants of Rezin, the descendants
        of Nekoda, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'the descendants of Gazzam, the descendants of Uzza, the descendants
        of Paseah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'the descendants of Besai, the descendants of Meunim, the descendants
        of Nephushesim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'the descendants of Bakbuk, the descendants of Hakupha, the descendants
        of Harhur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'the descendants of Bazlith, the descendants of Mehida, the descendants
        of Harsha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'the descendants of Barkos, the descendants of Sisera, the descendants
        of Temah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'the descendants of Neziah, the descendants of Hatipha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "The descendants of Solomon\u2019s servants: the descendants of Sotai,
        the descendants of Sophereth, the descendants of Perida, "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'the descendants of Jaala, the descendants of Darkon, the descendants
        of Giddel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'the descendants of Shephatiah, the descendants of Hattil, the descendants
        of Pochereth-Hazzebaim, the descendants of Amon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "All the temple servants and the descendants of Solomon\u2019s servants
        were three hundred and ninety-two. "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'These were the ones who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub,
        Addon, and Immer, but they were not able to prove their ancestral houses
        or their descent, whether they were from Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'the descendants of Delaiah, the descendants of Tobiah, the descendants
        of Nekoda, six hundred and forty-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And from the priests: the descendants of Hobaiah, the descendants
        of Hakkoz, the descendants of Barzillai (who had taken as a wife from the
        daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name). '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'These sought their record among those enrolled in the genealogy,
        but it was not found there, so they were excluded as unclean from the priesthood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'So the governor said to them that they could not eat the most holy
        food until a priest could come with Urim and Thummim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'All of the assembly together was forty-two thousand three hundred
        and sixty, '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "besides their servants and female slaves\u2014these were seven thousand
        three hundred and thirty-seven. And the male and female singers were two
        hundred and forty-five,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: ' there were four hundred and thirty-five camels and six thousand
        seven hundred and twenty male donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'Now some from the heads of the families gave to the work. The governor
        gave to the storehouse one thousand darics of gold, fifty basins, and five
        hundred and thirty priestly tunics. '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: 'Now some of the heads of the families gave to the storehouse of the
        work twenty thousand gold darics and two thousand two hundred silver minas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: 'And what the rest of the people gave was twenty thousand darics of
        gold, and two thousand silver minas, and sixty-seven priestly tunics. '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of
        the people, the temple servants, and all Israel settled in their cities.
        When the seventh month came, the Israelites were in their cities. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ezra Reads the Law to the People'
      title: Ezra Reads the Law to the People
      number: 1
      content: 'All of the people gathered as one to the public square before the
        Water Gate. They asked Ezra the scribe to bring the book of the law of Moses
        that Yahweh had commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Ezra the priest brought the law before the assembly for each man
        and woman to hear with understanding, on the first day of the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He read from it facing the public square before the Water Gate from
        dawn until noon that day, opposite the men, women, and those with understanding.
        The ears of all the people were attentive to the book of the law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Ezra the scribe stood on a wooden podium that had been made
        for the occasion. And beside him stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah,
        Hilkiah, and Maaseiah on his right. On his left was Pedaiah, Mishael, Malkijah,
        Hashum, Hashbaddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, because he was
        above all of the people. When he opened it all the people stood up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Ezra blessed Yahweh the great God, and all of the people answered,
        \u201CAmen! Amen!\u201D while lifting their hands. Then they bowed down and
        worshiped Yahweh with their noses to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah,
        Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites were teaching the
        people from the law while the people were in their places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So they read the book from the law of God, making it clear and giving
        the meaning so that they could understand the reading. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Nehemiah the governor, Ezra the priest and scribe, and the Levites
        who taught the people said to all of the people, \u201CThis day is holy to
        Yahweh your God. Do not mourn nor weep.\u201D For all of the people wept
        when they heard the words of the law.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CGo, eat festive food and drink sweet
        drinks, and send a share to those for whom nothing is prepared; for this
        day is holy to our lord. Do not be grieved because the joy of Yahweh is your
        refuge.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Levites silenced all of the people, saying, \u201CSilence,
        for this day is holy. Do not be grieved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Festival of Booths'
      title: Festival of Booths
      number: 12
      content: 'All of the people went to eat, to drink, to send a share, and to
        have great joy because they understood the words that they had made known
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On the second day the heads of the families of all the people, the
        priests, and the Levites gathered together to Ezra the scribe to study the
        words of the law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They found written in the law, which Yahweh had commanded by the
        hand of Moses, that the Israelites should live in booths during the festival
        of the seventh month, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and that they should proclaim and give voice in all of their cities
        in Jerusalem, saying, \u201CGo out to the hill and bring olive tree branches,
        olive oil wood branches, myrtle shrub branches, palm tree branches, and other
        leafy tree branches to make booths, as it is written.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the people went out and brought them and made booths for themselves,
        each on his roof, in their courtyards, in the courtyards of the house of
        God, in the public square of the Water Gate, and in the public square of
        the Gate of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And all of the assembly of those who returned from captivity made
        booths and lived in the booths because the Israelites had not done it from
        the days of Jeshua son of Nun until that day. And there was very great joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he read from the scroll of the law of God day by day from the
        first day up to the last day. They celebrated the festival for seven days,
        and on the eighth day there was an assembly according to the rule. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Nation Confesses'
      title: The Nation Confesses
      number: 1
      content: 'On the twenty-fourth day of this month the Israelites gathered in
        fasting, in sackcloths, and with soil on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Those of the seed of Israel separated themselves from all of the
        foreigners and stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their
        ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They stood up in their place and read from the book of the law of
        Yahweh their God for a fourth part of the day, and for a fourth they were
        confessing and worshiping Yahweh their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and
        Kenani stood on the platform of the Levites and cried out with a loud voice
        to Yahweh their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah,
        Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah said, \u201CStand up, bless Yahweh your
        God from everlasting until everlasting. Blessed be your glorious name that
        is being exalted above all blessing and praise! "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou alone are Yahweh. You alone have made the heavens, the
        heavens of the heavens, and all of their army, the earth and all that is
        in it, the waters and all that is in them. You give life to all of them,
        and the army of the heavens worship you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You are Yahweh, the God who chose Abram and brought him from Ur of
        the Chaldeans and named him Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You found his heart faithful before you and made a covenant with
        him to give the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Perizzite,
        the Jebusite and the Girgashite\u2014to give it to his seed. And you have
        kept your word because you are righteous. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou saw the misery of our ancestors in Egypt, and you heard
        their shout at the Red Sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You gave signs and wonders against Pharaoh, all of his servants,
        and all of the people of his land because you knew that they acted arrogantly
        against them. You made a name for yourself, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you divided the sea before them, and they passed through the
        sea on dry ground, but their pursuers you threw into the depths like a stone
        into mighty waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You led them by day with a column of cloud and with a column of fire
        by night, to give them light on the way that they were to go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you came down on Mount Sinai and spoke with them from heaven
        and gave them right judgments and true teachings, good regulations and commandments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You made known your holy Sabbath to them and gave them commandments,
        regulations, and law by the hand of your servant Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You gave them bread from heaven for their starvation, and you caused
        water to go out from a rock for their thirst. You told them to go in order
        to take into possession the land that you have sworn by your hand to give
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut they and our ancestors acted arrogantly and stiffened their
        neck and did not listen to your commandments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They refused to listen and did not remember your wonders that you
        did among them. They stiffened their neck and in their rebellion determined
        to return to their slavery. But you are a God of forgiveness, gracious and
        compassionate, slow to anger, abundant in loyal love, so you did not abandon
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Even when they made for themselves a molten idol of a calf and said,
        \u2018This is your God who brought you out from Egypt,\u2019 and committed
        great blasphemies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But you in your many mercies did not abandon them in the desert.
        The column of cloud that was over them in the day did not cease to leave
        them on the way, and the column of fire by night that gave light to them
        on the way that they went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And you gave your good Spirit to instruct them and did not withhold
        your manna from their mouth and gave them water for their thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Forty years you sustained them in the desert\u2014they were not in
        need. Their clothing did not wear out and their feet did not swell. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you gave them kingdoms and nations and allotted them a portion.
        They took into possession the land of Sihon king of Heshbon and the land
        of Og king of Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You made their children numerous like the stars of the heavens and
        brought them to the land that you told their ancestors to enter in order
        to take possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the children went in and took possession of the land. You subdued
        before them the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites; you gave them into
        their hand, and their kings and the nations of the land to do with them according
        to their pleasure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they captured fortified cities and a fertile land and took possession
        of houses filled with every good thing: hewn cisterns, vineyards, olive groves,
        and many fruit trees. They ate and became full, and they became fat and took
        delight in your great goodness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBut they rebelled and were rebellious against you and cast
        your law behind their back and killed your prophets, who had warned them
        to turn back to you, and they did great blasphemies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Therefore you gave them into the hand of their enemy, and they brought
        trouble to them. Then in the time of their trouble they cried out to you,
        and you heard from the heavens, and according to your great compassions,
        you gave them saviors, and you saved them from the hand of their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But when they had rest they returned to doing evil before you, and
        you abandoned them in the hand of their enemies, and they ruled over them.
        Then they returned and cried out to you, and from the heavens you heard and
        many times rescued them according to your compassions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You warned them so that they would return to your law. Yet they acted
        arrogantly and did not listen to your commandments but sinned against your
        judgments that a person must do so that they may live. They turned a stubborn
        shoulder and stiffened their neck and would not listen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You were patient toward them for many years, and you have warned
        them by your spirit through the hand of your prophets, but they did not listen.
        So you gave them into the hand of the nations of the lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But in your great compassions you did not put an end to them, and
        you did not abandon them. For you are a gracious and compassionate God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CAnd now our God, the great, mighty, and awesome God who keeps
        his covenant and loyal love, do not belittle in your presence all of the
        hardship that is found in us, our kings, our officials, our priests, our
        prophets, our ancestors, and all of our people, from the days of the kings
        of Assyria until this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'You are righteous in everything that has come on us, for you dealt
        faithfully, and we have acted wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Our kings, our officials, our priests, and our ancestors did not
        keep your law and did not listen to your commandments and statutes that you
        declared to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And in their kingdom and in the greatness you gave to them, and in
        the wide and fertile land that you gave before them, they did not serve you
        and did not turn from their evil deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Behold, we are slaves to this day, and the land that you have given
        to our ancestors to eat its fruits and enjoy its goodness\u2014behold, we
        are slaves in it! "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Its rich yield goes to the kings whom you have given over us because
        of our sins, and they are ruling over our dead bodies and our livestock at
        their pleasure. We are in great trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: " \u201CNow because of all of this we make a binding written agreement
        and are writing on the sealed documents the names of our commanders, our
        Levites, and our priests.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Names of Those Who Signed the Covenant'
      title: The Names of Those Who Signed the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: 'Upon the sealed documents: Nehemiah the governor, son of Hacaliah
        and Zedekiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Pashhur, Amariah, Malkijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah\u2014these are the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Levites: Jeshua son of Azaniah, Binnui from the sons of Henadad,
        Kadmiel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'their brothers Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Zaccur, Shereiah, Shebanaih, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hodiah, Bani, Beninu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The heads of the people: Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hariph, Anathoth, Nobai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ahijah, Hanan, Anan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: A Summary of the Covenant'
      title: A Summary of the Covenant
      number: 27
      content: 'Malluch, Harim, Baanah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThe rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers,
        the singers, the temple servants, and all who separated themselves from the
        peoples of the lands to observe the law of God\u2014their wives, their sons,
        their daughters, and all who know and understand\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'are helping their brothers, their nobles, and entering into a solemn
        oath to walk in the law of God which was given by the hand of Moses the servant
        of God, and to observe and do all of the commandments of Yahweh our Lord
        and his judgments and regulations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'We will not give our daughters to the peoples of the land nor take
        their daughters for our sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the peoples of the land who bring merchandise and any grain on
        the Sabbath day to sell, we will not accept it from them on the Sabbath or
        on a holy day. We will forego the crops of the seventh year and cancel every
        debt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CWe put on ourselves the commandment upon us to yearly give
        a third of a shekel for the service of the house of our God: "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'for the rows of bread, the offering of the daily sacrifice, the continual
        burnt sacrifice, the Sabbaths, the new moon festivals, the appointed festival
        times, the holy objects, the sin offerings that make atonement for Israel,
        and for all the work of the house of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And we have cast lots for the contributions of the wood offering
        of the priests, the Levites, and the people to bring it to the house of our
        God, by our fathers\u2019 houses, at designated times, year by year, to burn
        on the altar of Yahweh our God\u2014as it is written in the law.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'We also bring the first fruits of our soil and the first fruits of
        all the fruit trees, year by year, for the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And the firstborn of our sons and beasts\u2014as it is written in
        the law\u2014and the firstborn of our cattle and sheep, to bring to the house
        of our God and to the priests serving in the house of our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And we bring the best of our dough, our offerings, the fruit of every
        tree, new wine, and olive oil to the priests, to the chambers of the house
        of our God; and to bring the tithe of our soil to the Levites, for the Levites
        receive the tithes in all of our rural towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the priest, the descendant of Aaron, will be with the Levites
        during the tithe the Levites receive. The Levites will bring up a tithe of
        the tithes for the house of our God to the chambers of the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For the Israelites and the Levites will bring to the storerooms the
        offering of grain, new wine, and olive oil. These are the objects of the
        sanctuary and the priests who minister and the gatekeepers and singers. We
        will not neglect the house of our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Leaders and Servants in Jerusalem'
      title: The Leaders and Servants in Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "Now the commanders of the people lived in Jerusalem, but the remainder
        of the people cast lots to bring one out of ten to live in the holy city
        of Jerusalem, the other nine\u2019s place was in the other cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the people blessed all the men who willingly offered to live
        in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "These are the heads of the province who lived in Jerusalem, but in
        the cities of Judah each one lived on his property in their cities: Israel,
        the priests, the Levites, the temple servants, and the descendants of Solomon\u2019s
        servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And some from the descendants of Judah and Benjamin lived in Jerusalem.
        From the descendants of Judah: Athaiah son of Uzziah, son of Zechariah, son
        of Amariah, son of Shephatiah, son of Mahalalel, from the descendants of
        Perez; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Maaseiah son of Baruch, son of Col-Hozeh, son of Hazaiah, son
        of Adaiah, son of Jehoiarib, son of Zechariah, son of the Shilonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All of the descendants of Perez who were living in Jerusalem were
        four hundred and sixty-eight able-bodied men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These are the descendants of Benjamin: Sallu son of Meshullam, son
        of Joed, son of Pedaiah, son of Kolaiah, son of Maaseiah, son of Ithiel,
        son of Jeshaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And following after him Gabbai, Sallai, nine hundred and twenty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joel son of Zicri, their chief officer; and Judah son of Hassenuah,
        second in command over the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From the priests: Jedaiah son of Jehoiarib, Jakin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Seraiah son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of Meraioth,
        son of Ahitub\u2014the leader of the house of God\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and their brothers who did the work of the house, eight hundred and
        twenty-two. And Adaiah son of Jeroham, son of Pelaliah, son of Amzi, son
        of Zechariah, son of Pashhur, son of Malkijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and his brothers, heads of the families, two hundred and forty-two.
        And Amashai son of Azarel, son of Ahzai, son of Meshillemoth, son of Immer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and their brothers; mighty warriors of strength, one hundred and
        twenty-eight. The chief officer over them was Zabdiel son of Hagedolim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now from the Levites: Shemaiah son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son
        of Hashabiah, son of Bunni; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Shabbethai and Jehozabad, leaders over the work of the Levites
        outside of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Mattaniah son of Micah, son of Zabdi, son of Asaph, who was the leader
        to begin the thanksgiving prayer, and Bakbukiah the second of his brothers;
        Abda son of Shammua, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All of the Levites in the holy city were two hundred and eighty-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The gatekeepers: Akkub, Talmon, and their brothers, the keepers of
        the gates, one hundred and seventy-two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the remainder of Israel, the priests and the Levites, in all
        of the cities of Judah, each in his inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the temple servants were living on the Ophel; Ziha and Gishpa
        were over the temple servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The chief officer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi son of Bani,
        son of Hashabiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Mica, from the descendants of
        Asaph, the singers over the work of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For there was a command of the king concerning them and a regulation
        concerning the singers, required day by day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Villages Outside of Jerusalem'
      title: Villages Outside of Jerusalem
      number: 24
      content: 'And Pethahiah son of Meshezabel, from the descendants of Zerah the
        son of Judah, was at the hand of the king in all matters concerning the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As for the villages in their territories, some from the descendants
        of Judah lived in Kiriath-Arba and its settlements, Dibon and its settlements,
        Jekabzeel and its settlements,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Jeshua, Moladah, Beth Pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hazar Shual, Beersheba and its settlements,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ziklad, Meconah and its settlements,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'En-Rimmon, Zorah, Jarmuch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Zanoah, Adullam and their settlements, Lachish and its fields, and
        Azekah and its settlements. So they camped from Beersheba up to the Valley
        of Hinnom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The descendants of Benjamin from Geba, Micmash, Aija, Bethel and
        their settlements,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Lod, and Ono the valley of the artisans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And from the Levites the working groups of Judah were assigned to
        Benjamin. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Leaders and Servants in Jerusalem'
      title: The Leaders and Servants in Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the priests and the Levites who came up with Zerubbabel
        son of Shealtiel and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shemaiah, Jehoiarib, Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These are the heads of the priests
        and their brothers in the days of Jeshua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah
        and his brothers who were in charge of the songs of thanksgiving. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Bakbukiah, Unno, their brothers stood opposite them during service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Jeshua fathered Jehoiakim; Jehoiakim fathered Eliashib; Eliashib
        fathered Jehoiada; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Jehoiada fathered Jehonathan; Jehonathan fathered Jaddua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now in the days of Jehoiakim the priests and the heads of the families
        were: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'of Melichu, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'of Adaia, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'of Abijah, Zicri; of Miniamin; of Moadiah, Piltai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'of Jehoiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'of Sallu, Kallai; of Amok, Eber; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; and of Jedaiah, Nethanel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In the days of Eliashib, Jehoiada, Jehohanan, and Jaddua the Levites
        were recorded as heads of the families. So these were the priests during
        the reign of Darius the Persian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The descendants of Levi and the heads of the families were recorded
        in the scroll of the Annals until the days of Jehohanan son of Eliashib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the heads of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, Jeshua son of
        Kadmiel, and their brothers opposite them, to praise and to give thanks by
        the command of David the man of God, section alongside section. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were
        gatekeepers standing guard at the storerooms of the gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Dedication of the Wall of Jerusalem'
      title: Dedication of the Wall of Jerusalem
      number: 26
      content: 'These were in the days of Jehoiakim son of Jeshua, son of Jehozadak,
        and in the days of Nehemiah the governor and Ezra the priest and scribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'At the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites
        from all of their places in order to bring them to Jerusalem to do the dedication
        with joy, thanksgivings, song and cymbals, stringed instruments and lyres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The singers were gathered from the circuit all around Jerusalem and
        from the villages of Netophathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'from Beth Gilgal, from the field of Geba and Azmaveth; for the singers
        built for themselves villages all around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the priests and the Levites purified themselves and purified
        the people, the gates, and the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then I brought the commanders of Judah up on to the wall. I appointed
        two great choirs; one went in a procession to the right on the wall to the
        Dung Gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'After them went Hoshaiah, half of the commanders of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'and the priests with trumpets; Zechariah son of Jehonathan, son of
        Shemaiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Micaiah, son of Zaccur, son of Asaph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his brothers Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel,
        Judah, and Hanani with the instruments of the songs of David the man of God;
        and Ezra the scribe went before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'At the Fountain Gate opposite them they went up the steps of the
        city of David, at the assent to the wall, over the house of David, and up
        to the Water Gate to the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the second choir went the opposite way. I followed after them
        with half of the people on the wall, from over the Tower of the Ovens up
        to the Wide Wall '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and over the Gate of Ephraim, at the Old Gate, at the Fish Gate,
        the Tower of Hananel and the Tower of the Hundred, and to the Sheep Gate.
        And they stopped and stood at the Gate of the Guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So the two choirs stood in the house of God, and I and half of the
        prefects with me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'and the priests Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah,
        and Hananiah with the trumpets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malkijah, Elam, and
        Ezer. And the singers sang with Jizrahiah the chief officer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Celebration at the Temple'
      title: Celebration at the Temple
      number: 43
      content: 'They offered on that day great sacrifices and rejoiced because God
        brought great joy to them. And the women and children also rejoiced. The
        joy of Jerusalem was heard from afar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On that day men were appointed for the storehouse rooms, the offerings,
        the first fruits, and the tithes, in order to gather in them from the fields
        of the cities the requirements of the law for the priests and Levites; for
        the joy of Judah was upon the priests and Levites standing there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'They kept the responsibility of their God and the responsibility
        of cleansing, and the singers and gatekeepers, according to the command of
        David and his son Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For in the days of David and Asaph from ancient times there was the
        head of the singers and a song of praise and thanksgiving to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'So all of Israel in the days of Zerubbabel and in the days of Nehemiah
        gave the daily food portions of the singers and gatekeepers. And they set
        apart that which was for the Levites, and the Levites set apart that which
        was for the descendants of Aaron. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Separates Itself'
      title: Israel Separates Itself
      number: 1
      content: 'On that day the book of Moses was read in the hearing of the people
        and it was found written in it that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever come
        into the assembly of God '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "because they did not come to meet the Israelites with bread and water,
        but hired Balaam against them in order to curse them\u2014but our God changed
        the curse into a blessing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Nehemiah Brings Reform'
      title: Nehemiah Brings Reform
      number: 3
      content: 'So it happened when they heard the law that they separated all of
        the foreign people from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Before this, Eliashib the priest who was appointed over the chambers
        of the house of our God\u2014the one related to Tobiah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'prepared for Tobiah a large chamber where they had formerly put the
        grain offering, the frankincense, the temple objects, tithes of grain, wine,
        and oil commanded for the Levites, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the
        offerings of the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'During all of this, I was not in Jerusalem because in the thirty-second
        year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon I went to the king. At the end of some
        days I asked permission from the king to leave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I came to Jerusalem. And I came to learn of the wrong that Eliashib
        had done for Tobiah by making him a room in the courtyard of the house of
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It was very displeasing for me, and I threw all of the objects from
        the house of Tobiah outside of the chamber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I spoke in order, and they cleansed the chambers. Then I returned
        the objects of the house of God\u2014the grain offering and the frankincense. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And then I came to learn that the food of the Levites had not been
        given to them, so that the Levites and the singers, the doers of the work,
        had gone back each to his field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So I quarreled with the prefects, and I said, \u201CWhy is the house
        of God forsaken?\u201D And I gathered them and set them at their station. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So all of Judah brought the tithe of grain, new wine, and olive oil
        into the storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I appointed as treasurer over the storehouses Shelemiah the priest,
        Zadok the scribe, Pedaiah from the Levites, and as their hand Hanan son of
        Zaccur, son of Mattaniah, for they were considered faithful. The responsibility
        given to them was to distribute to their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Nehemiah Begins Sabbath Reforms'
      title: Nehemiah Begins Sabbath Reforms
      number: 14
      content: 'Remember me, my God, concerning this, and do not wipe out my loyal
        acts which I have done in the house of my God and in his service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days I saw in Judah people treading the wine press on the
        Sabbath, bringing in heaps of grain and loading them on donkeys along with
        wine, grapes and figs, and every kind of burden and bringing it all to Jerusalem
        on the day of the Sabbath. And I warned them at that time against selling
        food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Tyrian men who lived in Jerusalem brought fish and every kind of
        merchandise and sold it on the Sabbath to the descendants of Judah and in
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I quarreled with the nobles of Judah and said to them, \u201CWhat
        is this evil thing that you are doing, profaning the day of the Sabbath? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Did not your ancestors do this also, and our God brought on us all
        of this disaster and on this city too? Now you are adding fierce wrath on
        Israel by profaning the Sabbath!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So when it became dark at the gates of Jerusalem before the Sabbath,
        I commanded that the doors be shut and said that they should not be opened
        until after the Sabbath. And I appointed some of my young men over the gates
        to prevent any goods being brought in on the day of the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the merchants and the sellers of merchandise spent the night outside
        of Jerusalem once or twice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But I warned them and said to them, \u201CWhy are you spending the
        night opposite the wall? If you do it again, I will lay hands against you.\u201D
        From that time on they did not come on the Sabbath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Mixed Marriages are Condemned'
      title: Mixed Marriages are Condemned
      number: 22
      content: 'And then I told two Levites that they must purify themselves and
        come to guard the gates in order to consecrate the day of the Sabbath. Remember
        this also, my God, and take pity on me according to the greatness of your
        loyal love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Also in those days I saw Jews who had married women of Ashdod, Ammon,
        and Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Half of their children spoke Ashdodite and could not speak Judean,
        but only the tongues of other nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So I quarreled with them and cursed them and beat some of their men
        and pulled out their hair. I made them take an oath by God: \u201CDo not
        give your daughters to their sons or take their daughters for your sons or
        for yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Did not King Solomon of Israel sin in this way? And among the many
        nations there was no king like him, and he was beloved by his God, and God
        made him king over all Israel. Yet the foreign women made even him sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Should we listen to you all and do this great evil, acting unfaithfully
        against our God by marrying foreign women?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'One from the sons of Jehoiada, son of the high priest Eliashib, who
        was the son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonote was there. I chased him away
        from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Remember them, my God, because of their defilements of the priesthood
        and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So I cleansed them from everything foreign, and I established responsibilities
        for the priests and Levites, each in his own work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'a contribution of the wood offering at appointed times, and for the
        first fruits. Remember me, my God, for good. '
      comments: []
